3557	  % SOURCE QUOTE: "Let $X$ be a ringed space.
3558	  % Let $\mathcal{U} : U = \bigcup_{i \in I} U_i$ be an open covering.
3559	  % Let $\mathcal{I}$ be an injective $\mathcal{O}_X$-module.
3560	  % Then
3561	  % $$
3562	  % \check{H}^p(\mathcal{U}, \mathcal{I}) =
3563	  % \left\{
3564	  % \begin{matrix}
3565	  % \mathcal{I}(U) & \text{if} & p = 0 \\
