3570	  \textit{Source: Stacks Project, Cohomology, \texttt{lemma-injective-trivial-cech}.}
3571	  Every injective \(\mathcal{O}_X\)-module \(\mathcal{I}\) has vanishing positive-degree {\v C}ech
3572	  cohomology over a standard cover \emph{of the whole affine}: if
3573	  \(s : \iota \to R\) spans, \(\operatorname{span}(\operatorname{range} s) = \top\), so that the
3574	  distinguished opens \(D(s_i)\) cover \(\operatorname{Spec} R\), then
3575	  \(\check{H}^p(\mathcal{U}, \mathcal{I}) = 0\) for every \(p > 0\). This is the special case of the
3576	  family-form injective {\v C}ech-acyclicity (Lemma~\ref{lem:injective_cech_acyclic}) at the
3577	  spanning family \(s\); the general \(\mathrm{injective\_acyclic}\) field of the affine cover system
3578	  is discharged by that family-form lemma directly.
3579	\end{lemma}
3580	\begin{proof}
3581	  \uses{lem:injective_cech_acyclic, lem:cover_datum_bridge}
3582	  \leanok
3583	  The opens of the standard cover \(\mathcal{U}\) attached to the spanning family \(s\) are the
3584	  distinguished opens \(D(s_i)\) (Lemma~\ref{lem:cover_datum_bridge}). Applying the family-form
3585	  injective {\v C}ech-acyclicity (Lemma~\ref{lem:injective_cech_acyclic}) to the finite family
3586	  \(i \mapsto D(s_i)\) gives \(\check{H}^p(\mathcal{U}, \mathcal{I}) = 0\) for all \(p > 0\).
3587	\end{proof}
